      "message": "The semantics of this are odd, now (but not necessarily wrong or not useful). If the dst is flagged for nonlinear blend, this does two of the three steps to go from src to dst (gamut and dst TF), but skips the src TF. The assumption is that the input floats are actually linear (in src gamut), but the output floats are nonlinear (in dst gamut and dst TF)?",
